Turkeyâ€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  was little changed at 60,725.88 at the close in Istanbul
after rising 6.2 percent last month.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Mardin Cimento Sanayii & Ticaret AS (MRDIN)  , a cement
producer, gained 1.3 percent to 6.44 liras after reporting 2011
profit was 84.2 million liras ($48 million), beating estimates.  Yapi Kredi Finansal Kiralama AS (YKFIN)  , the leasing
unit of  Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS (YKBNK) , surged 15 percent to 5.07 liras
after saying it will offer at least 5.02 liras per share to
minority shareholders as part of a plan to delist from the
